## Vercel CLI & MCP

- This project is deployed on Vercel. Account: `konradkaluzny-3520` (team: `konrads-projects`).
- Vercel CLI is installed globally. Use it for deployments, env vars, logs, and domain management.
- Always deploy to preview first (`vercel --yes`), verify, then promote to production (`vercel --prod --yes`).
- Use `--yes` flag to skip confirmation prompts.
- Never delete production deployments without explicit user confirmation.
- For environment variable changes, always specify the environment (`production`, `preview`, `development`).
- Use `vercel logs <url>` to debug deployment issues.
- Vercel MCP is configured at `.cursor/mcp.json` — use it for structured queries when available.
